    <solution><p>It<rsq/>s important to suppress any urge to expand the squared binomial.</p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
(q+2)^2-12\amp=0\\
(q+2)^2\amp=12\\
q+2\amp=\pm\sqrt{12}\\
q+2\amp=\pm\sqrt{4\cdot3}\\
q+2\amp=\pm2\sqrt{3}\\
q\amp=\pm2\sqrt{3}-2
\end{aligned}</me></p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
q\amp=-2\sqrt{3}-2\amp\text{or}\amp\amp q\amp=2\sqrt{3}-2
\end{aligned}</me></p>
<p>The solution set is <m>\left\{-2\sqrt{3}-2,2\sqrt{3}-2\right\}\text{.}</m></p>
</solution>
